<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="30Mar1926"><font color="red">30 March 1926</font> <i>BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver): Some (very little) sight is coming into my eye &hellip; I also enclose a letter from Hemingway which seems to knock on the head my plan for sale of <b><font face="wake">D</font></b>abcd. I am working hard on him and am delighted with the four facets of his character. It will all hang together and it can go up for the auction &hellip; I am ploughing through [Lewis&apos;s] book but have not yet finished it so as to know what I am doing <i>dans ??cette gal&egrave;re</i>. Anyhow it is plain from the cuttings you sent that his slogan (Mr Joyce and Mr Jingle) had gone around. I am replying to this in a most grotesque addition to <b><font face="wake">D</font></b>b </div>
